I am pleased to announce my office’s inaugural participation in the Congressional App Challenge.
 
The Congressional App Challenge is a national event, where students in Congressional Districts across the country can compete to create internet applications (apps) developing their coding and software design skills. 
 
Students may submit apps dealing with any topic prior to November 1, 2023.  

Contestants may compete individually, or in teams of up to four participants.
 
Please visit the Congressional App Challenge Web Page at congressionalappchallenge.us… to register. 

If you have any questions about this annual challenge, please contact my office at 202-225-5311 and ask for our App Challenge Coordinator.
